:"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.html#PowerSeries.invOneSubPow_inv_eq_one_sub_pow","kind":"theorem","line":149,"name":"PowerSeries.invOneSubPow_inv_eq_one_sub_pow","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.lean#L149-L153"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.html#PowerSeries.invOneSubPow_eq_inv_one_sub_pow\"><span class=\"name\">PowerSeries</span>.<span class=\"name\">invOneSubPow_eq_inv_one_sub_pow</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">S</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">S</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">d</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.html#PowerSeries.invOneSubPow\">invOneSubPow</a> <span class=\"fn\">S</span> <span class=\"fn\">d</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Units/Defs.html#Units.mkOfMulEqOne\">Units.mkOfMulEqOne</a> (<span class=\"fn\">1</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSub.hSub\">-</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/Basic.html#PowerSeries.X\">X</a>) <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/Basic.html#PowerSeries.mk\">mk</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">⋯</span>)</span><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Inv.inv\">⁻¹</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> <span class=\"fn\">d</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The theorem `PowerSeries.mk_one_mul_one_sub_eq_one` implies that `1 - X` is a unit in `S⟦X⟧`\nwhose inverse is the power series `1 + X + X^2 + ...`. This theorem states that for any `d : ℕ`,\n`PowerSeries.invOneSubPow S d` is equal to `(1 - X)⁻¹ ^ d`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.html#PowerSeries.invOneSubPow_eq_inv_one_sub_pow","kind":"theorem","line":132,"name":"PowerSeries.invOneSubPow_eq_inv_one_sub_pow","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.lean#L132-L147"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.html#PowerSeries.invOneSubPow_val_one_eq_invUnitSub_one\"><span class=\"name\">PowerSeries</span>.<span class=\"name\">invOneSubPow_val_one_eq_invUnitSub_one</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">S</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">S</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.html#PowerSeries.invOneSubPow\">invOneSubPow</a> <span class=\"fn\">S</span> <span class=\"fn\">1</span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.html#PowerSeries.invUnitsSub\">invUnitsSub</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.html#PowerSeries.invOneSubPow_val_one_eq_invUnitSub_one","kind":"theorem","line":128,"name":"PowerSeries.invOneSubPow_val_one_eq_invUnitSub_one","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.lean#L128-L130"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.html#PowerSeries.invOneSubPow_val_succ_eq_mk_add_choose\"><span class=\"name\">PowerSeries</span>.<span class=\"name\">invOneSubPow_val_succ_eq_mk_add_choose</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">S</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">S</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">d</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.html#PowerSeries.invOneSubPow\">invOneSubPow</a> <span class=\"fn\">S</span> (<span class=\"fn\">d</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAdd.hAdd\">+</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span>))</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/Basic.html#PowerSeries.mk\">mk</a> <span class=\"fn\">fun (<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">d</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAdd.hAdd\">+</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span>).<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Nat/Choose/Basic.html#Nat.choose\">choose</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">d</span>)</span></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.html#PowerSeries.invOneSubPow_val_succ_eq_mk_add_choose","kind":"theorem","line":125,"name":"PowerSeries.invOneSubPow_val_succ_eq_mk_add_choose","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.lean#L125-L126"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.html#PowerSeries.invOneSubPow_val_eq_mk_sub_one_add_choose_of_pos\"><span class=\"name\">PowerSeries</span>.<span class=\"name\">invOneSubPow_val_eq_mk_sub_one_add_choose_of_pos</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">S</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">S</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">d</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h</span> : <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\">d</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.html#PowerSeries.invOneSubPow\">invOneSubPow</a> <span class=\"fn\">S</span> <span class=\"fn\">d</span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/Basic.html#PowerSeries.mk\">mk</a> <span class=\"fn\">fun (<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">d</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSub.hSub\">-</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAdd.hAdd\">+</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span>).<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Nat/Choose/Basic.html#Nat.choose\">choose</a></span> (<span class=\"fn\">d</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSub.hSub\">-</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span>))</span></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.html#PowerSeries.invOneSubPow_val_eq_mk_sub_one_add_choose_of_pos","kind":"theorem","line":121,"name":"PowerSeries.invOneSubPow_val_eq_mk_sub_one_add_choose_of_pos","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.lean#L121-L123"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.html#PowerSeries.invOneSubPow_zero\"><span class=\"name\">PowerSeries</span>.<span class=\"name\">invOneSubPow_zero</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">S</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">S</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.html#PowerSeries.invOneSubPow\">invOneSubPow</a> <span class=\"fn\">S</span> <span class=\"fn\">0</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.html#PowerSeries.invOneSubPow_zero","kind":"theorem","line":117,"name":"PowerSeries.invOneSubPow_zero","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.lean#L117-L119"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">noncomputable def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.html#PowerSeries.invOneSubPow\"><span class=\"name\">PowerSeries</span>.<span class=\"name\">invOneSubPow</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">S</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">S</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a> → <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/Basic.html#PowerSeries\">PowerSeries</a> <span class=\"fn\">S</span>)</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Units/Defs.html#Units\">ˣ</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given a natural number `d : ℕ` and a commutative ring `S`, `PowerSeries.invOneSubPow S d` is the\nmultiplicative inverse of `(1 - X) ^ d` in `S⟦X⟧ˣ`. When `d` is `0`, `PowerSeries.invOneSubPow S d`\nwill just be `1`. When `d` is positive, `PowerSeries.invOneSubPow S d` will be the power series\n`mk fun n => Nat.choose (d - 1 + n) (d - 1)`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.html#PowerSeries.invOneSubPow","kind":"def","line":100,"name":"PowerSeries.invOneSubPow","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.lean#L100-L115"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.html#PowerSeries.mk_one_pow_eq_mk_choose_add\"><span class=\"name\">PowerSeries</span>.<span class=\"name\">mk_one_pow_eq_mk_choose_add</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">S</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">S</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">d</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/Basic.html#PowerSeries.mk\">mk</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> (<span class=\"fn\">d</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAdd.hAdd\">+</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span>) <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/Basic.html#PowerSeries.mk\">mk</a> <span class=\"fn\">fun (<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">d</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAdd.hAdd\">+</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span>).<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Nat/Choose/Basic.html#Nat.choose\">choose</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">d</span>)</span></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Note that `mk 1` is the constant function `1` so the power series `1 + X + X^2 + ...`. This theorem\nstates that for any `d : ℕ`, `(1 + X + X^2 + ... : S⟦X⟧) ^ (d + 1)` is equal to the power series\n`mk fun n => Nat.choose (d + n) d : S⟦X⟧`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.html#PowerSeries.mk_one_pow_eq_mk_choose_add","kind":"theorem","line":84,"name":"PowerSeries.mk_one_pow_eq_mk_choose_add","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.lean#L84-L98"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.html#PowerSeries.mk_one_mul_one_sub_eq_one\"><span class=\"name\">PowerSeries</span>.<span class=\"name\">mk_one_mul_one_sub_eq_one</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">S</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">S</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/Basic.html#PowerSeries.mk\">mk</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> (<span class=\"fn\">1</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSub.hSub\">-</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/Basic.html#PowerSeries.X\">X</a>) <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"(1 + X + X^2 + ...) * (1 - X) = 1.\n\nNote that the power series `1 + X + X^2 + ...` is written as `mk 1` where `1` is the constant\nfunction so that `mk 1` is the power series with all coefficients equal to one.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.html#PowerSeries.mk_one_mul_one_sub_eq_one","kind":"theorem","line":71,"name":"PowerSeries.mk_one_mul_one_sub_eq_one","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.lean#L71-L82"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"